<P>
 LAKE TRAGEDY: To 10-year-old Ninoy Kiat of Panorama City, the ice-covered lake 
looked like a fun place to play. But he soon fell into the freezing water of 
Lake Jackson, near Wrightwood, prompting his mother to frantically run onto the 
thin ice after him.She, too, plunged into the water. . . . When it was all 
over, Ninoy was safe, but his mother, Analiza, was dead (B1). 
</P>
<P>
 OFF-ROAD DUSTUP: Motocross fans have their hearts set on an off-road vehicle 
park being built in rugged Baker and Hume canyons in Santa Clarita. But canyon 
homeowners are staunchly opposed, citing noise and traffic. . . . Opponents 
last week won a partial victory when county supervisors ruled Baker unsuitable 
for motocross. But Hume is still a possible site (B14). 
</P>
<P>
 PARTY SHOOTING: A 17-year-old alleged gang member was shot in the head by a 
state prison officer during a gun battle at a late-night Pacoima party. Four 
other party-goers were wounded when several shots were fired. . . . Police said 
the prison officer, who was not identified, apparently acted in self-defense 
when he shot the teen, reported in critical condition. (B3). 
</P>
<P>
 KING DAY EVENTS: The birthday of Martin Luther King Jr. will be observed 
today. Commemorations are scheduled throughout Los Angeles County, including 
several in the San Fernando Valley (B3). 
</P>
<P>
 TONIGHT: L. A. Cabaret, 17271 Ventura Blvd., Encino, offers comedy starting at 
7:30. Cover charge $6 plus a two-drink minimum per show. Info: (818) 501-3737. 
</P>
<P>
 WEATHER: Sunny and warmer with gusty winds below passes and canyons. Highs in 
70s (B7). 
