<P>
 TEEN TOWN: Bob Buckles wasn't surprised to learn that Fillmore has 
proportionately more teen-agers than any other Ventura County city. . . . "We 
do have a lot," said Buckles, whose job as recreation director is to keep them 
all busy. "It's a challenge. We do surveys to find out what they want." High on 
the wish list: a skating rink and bowling alley, neither of which is feasible 
in the small community. . . . One recent innovation is midnight basketball on 
weekends, an alternative to the street. Next month's schedule includes a youth 
car show. "The kids run the whole program. It's something for them to be in 
charge of." Where the Teens Are 
