<P>
 President Carlos Salinas de Gortari said he wants a general amnesty for all 
sides in a conflict in the southern state of Chiapas and ordered a special 
session of the Mexican Congress to consider the plan. He said the offer will 
give rebels who launched a New Year's Day uprising for indigenous rights no 
excuse not to lay down their arms. The newspaper La Jornada said the rebels, 
known as the Zapatista National Liberation Army, will respond to the 
government's call for dialogue soon and listed some of their goals. 
