<HEADLINE>
<P>
NBA ROUNDUP; TRAIL BLAZERS KEEP SAVING MURRAY'S BEST FOR LAST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Tracy Murray is making a habit of shooting down the Charlotte Hornets. 
</P>
<P>
 On Sunday night, Murray scored 11 points in the fourth quarter, leading the 
Portland Trail Blazers to a 106-101 victory over the Hornets at Portland. 
</P>
<P>
 Only two weeks ago, Murray had 22 points and made four of five three-point 
shots in 20 minutes of play in the Trail Blazers' 116-110 victory at Charlotte. 
</P>
<P>
 "I just want to make sure I keep myself mentally ready, especially when you 
come in the third and fourth quarters," Murray said. 
</P>
<P>
 Portland Coach Rick Adelman kept Murray on the sidelines until the start of 
the fourth quarter on Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 Murray made a three-point basket during an 9-0 run that helped the Trail 
Blazers come back from an 11-point third-quarter deficit. He also made a 
three-point play with 4:34 left that broke a 92-92 tie and gave the Trail 
Blazers the lead for good. 
</P>
<P>
 "Physically, all I have to do is run up and down the floor a couple of times 
and I'm ready," Murray said. 
</P>
<P>
 Clifford Robinson scored 20 points for the Trail Blazers. 
</P>
<P>
 Hersey Hawkins led the Hornets with 24 points. Alonzo Mourning added 20. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 New Jersey 99, Utah 94 -- The Nets held the Jazz without a basket over the 
final 6:41 at East Rutherford, N.J. 
</P>
<P>
 Kenny Anderson and Kevin Edwards combined for 20 of the 26 fourth-quarter 
points scored by the Nets, who played without starting forwards Derrick 
Coleman, who had back spasms, and Chris Morris, who had flu. 
</P>
<P>
 The Nets are 3-0 in games Coleman has sat out. 
</P>
<P>
 Anderson had 24 points, 14 assists, five rebounds and two steals. Edwards 
scored 25 points. 
</P>
<P>
 Anderson and Edwards each had 10 points during a fourth quarter that featured 
eight ties and two lead changes. 
</P>
<P>
 Karl Malone had 23 points for the Jazz, but only three in the final quarter. 
John Stockton had 17 points for the Jazz, who have lost five of six. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Boston 105, Denver 100 -- Rookie forward Dino Radja scored 29 points and 
Robert Parish had a season-best 26 at Boston as the Celtics ended their 
franchise-record seven-game home losing streak, and a five-game overall losing 
streak. 
</P>
<P>
 Dee Brown added 16 points and 11 assists and Xavier McDaniel had 12 points for 
the Celtics. 
</P>
<P>
 Mahmoud Abdul-Rauf led the Nuggets with 20 points. Tom Hammonds had 17, 
including 13 in the fourth quarter. The Nuggets are 5-15 on the road. 
</P>
<P>
 Hammonds had a chance to tie the score with 50 seconds left, but he missed a 
free throw. 
</P>
<P>
 A basket by Parish and a put-back by Radja with 10 seconds left helped seal 
the victory. 
</P>
