<HEADLINE>
<P>
VOLLEYBALL CLUB WINS TOURNAMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Mission Valley Blue 18-and-under girls' club volleyball team won the 
Fiesta Classic tournament by beating Arizona Juniors, 15-12, 15-2, in the 
championship match Sunday at Arizona State. 
</P>
<P>
 The team, which includes Analisa Saylor and Nina Foster of Mission Viejo, 
Jeanne Vetter of Dana Hills, Amy Steele of Laguna Hills, Hilary Kyle of Laguna 
Beach and Jennifer Kessy of Dana Hills, was undefeated in the tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 The Balboa Bay-Reebok boys' 18-and-under volleyball club team won three 
matches in pool play of the Berkeley Invitational Sunday at California. 
</P>
<P>
 The team, which includes Mitch McCoy, Eric Vallely and Paul Root of Newport 
Harbor High, Jeremy Darner of Dana Hills, Mike Grave of Huntington Beach, Tim 
Willey of Whittier Christian, Mike Allison of Esperanza and Brooks Hoppe of 
Corona del Mar, beat Clovis, 15-9, 15-7; Seaside of San Diego, 15-2, 11-15, 
15-10, and Santa Cruz, 8-15, 15-9, 15-12, and advanced into today's 
championship bracket as the top-seeded team. 
</P>
<P>
 The Balboa Bay White team also advanced to the championship bracket, beating 
White Rock of Vancouver, Canada, 15-12, 11-15, 15-10, City Beach of Berkeley, 
15-10, 16-14, and losing to Highline of Simi Valley, 9-15, 15-10, 15-9. 
</P>
