</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
BURNING FAT, DO-SI-DO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Square dancing is not just fun. It is not just a chance to socialize or show 
off that colorful new outfit. 
</P>
<P>
 No, this is Southern California, so members of the Sierra Hillbillies square 
dance club of Santa Clarita say their hobby is also a good way to get aerobic 
exercise. 
</P>
<P>
 According to the American Health Foundation, one hour of vigorous square 
dancing burns 560 calories -- more than tennis or bicycling -- as members of 
the group noted at a recent get-together. 
</P>
<P>
 Sounds like there may soon be a "Do-Si-Do Workout" video. 
</P>
<P>
 Meanwhile, the Sierra Hillbillies show up regularly in a high school cafeteria 
to burn off calories and have a good time too. 
</P>
<P>
 The 240-member club also offers classes for beginners. 
</P>
<P>
 Information on their activities and those of other square dance clubs in the 
area are listed in the Chatsworth-based publication Open Squares, which can be 
reached at (818) 993-4648. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA011794-0080 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 004819 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
January 17, 1994, Monday, Valley Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Metro; Part B; Page 3; Column 3 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
