<HEADLINE>
<P>
UCLA TIED WITH KANSAS AT THE TOP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 UCLA (11-0) and Kansas (16-1) are tied for the top spot in the USA Today/CNN 
coaches' poll that was released Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 Kansas received 13 first-place votes, UCLA 12. 
</P>
<P>
 Results of the Associated Press poll will be released today. 
</P>
<P>
 The last time the Bruins were ranked No. 1 was during the 1982-83 season, 
under Coach Larry Farmer, when they won 13 of their first 14 games and spent 
two weeks at the top of the AP poll. 
</P>
