<TEXT>
<P>
 Limits on Foreign Ownership to Remain: Finance Minister Hong Jai-hyung said in 
a radio report that the government will keep in place a regulation that limits 
the stake overseas investors may take in local companies to 10%.In an interview 
with the state-run KBS radio last week, Hong said the ceiling will remain 
intact for at least the first six months of this year. However, Hong declined 
to say when the adjustment will be made. The ministry has promised the U.S. 
government that the limit on investment will be relaxed this year. However, 
South Korean officials have been reluctant to raise the ceiling, saying that an 
increase in the influx of overseas funds will contribute to inflation. 
