<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN DIES TRYING TO BLOCK TRUCK TOWING HIS CAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LILY DIZON, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 27-year-old man who tried to keep his car from being towed died Saturday of 
injuries he suffered when the tow truck ran over him, police said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 Jorge Morales Lopez of Orange died of internal injuries at UCI Medical Center 
in Orange, said Lt. Robert Gustafson. 
</P>
<P>
 The tow truck driver, Russell Welch, 34, was not cited, police said. An 
investigation is continuing into the accident, which occurred at 8:30 p.m. at 
the Orange Eastridge Apartments, 121 E. Trenton Ave. 
</P>
<P>
 Gustafson said Lopez, who lived at the apartment complex, apparently parked 
his car on a private lot without the required parking sticker provided by the 
apartment managers. As his car was being towed, Lopez got into a shoving match 
with the driver towing his car, witnesses said. 
</P>
<P>
 Even after his car was hitched onto the tow truck, which drove slowly down the 
street, Lopez ran alongside the truck and threw punches at the driver, 
witnesses said. 
</P>
<P>
 At one point, "the victim was knocked to the ground and ran over by the tow 
vehicle," Gustafson said. 
</P>
<P>
 Few neighbors in this 24-unit complex saw the confrontation. Relatives and 
friends who shared the apartment with the victim declined to discuss the 
accident. 
</P>
<P>
 According to the manager of the apartment, Sebastian Pulido, Orange Eastridge 
has a contract with Tows R Russ of Orange to tow cars illegally parked in the 
lot, which is in the back of the apartment. 
</P>
<P>
 The towing company has a security officer who periodically patrols the lot, 
Pulido said. 
</P>
<P>
 The security guard apparently requested that Lopez's car be towed, Pulido 
added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA011794-0134 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 004892 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
January 17, 1994, Monday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
