<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: LA HABRA; COUNCILMAN JOINS STATE SENATOR'S STAFF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIMI KO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 City Councilman James Flora has taken a job as a field representative for 
state Sen. John R. Lewis (R-Orange). 
</P>
<P>
 Flora, 67, will work part time representing Lewis at community events in La 
Habra, Brea, Fullerton and Buena Park and deal with chambers of commerce, 
community organizations, city officials and businesses.He started the new job 
earlier this month, making $400 a month. 
</P>
<P>
 The retired Southern California Edison employee also serves as chairman of the 
county's Local Agency Formation Commission. Flora was appointed to the 
commission in 1988 and has served as chairman since May of last year, when 
Supervisor Don Roth resigned. 
</P>
<P>
 As chairman, Flora presides at LAFCO meetings. LAFCO's members have the power 
to approve the creation of cities or special districts and annexations. He said 
commissioners will be considering consolidating special districts in the coming 
year in an effort to reduce bureaucracy. 
</P>
<P>
 "I'm retired, so I have time" to hold two public offices and work for Lewis, 
Flora said. "I want to be involved and devote a lot more time to what I think I 
can do. And there's no conflict at all between the three jobs. . . . I'm glad 
I'm busy." MIMI KO 
</P>
</TEXT>
