<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: GARDEN GROVE; PLAN TO BUY A HOME? 2 PROGRAMS CAN HELP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The city is offering two programs giving financial assistance to first-time 
buyers who are purchasing a condominium, townhouse or single-family home in 
Garden Grove. 
</P>
<P>
 The city's Mortgage Credit Certificate allows qualified applicants to take up 
to 20% of the interest paid on the mortgage as a federal tax credit. 
</P>
<P>
 Also, the city has a Mortgage Assistance Program providing a down payment that 
can be as much as 10% of the purchase price of the home. 
</P>
<P>
 To be eligible, people must be buying a single-family home for use as their 
principal residence. Candidates also must be buying their first home and meet 
income requirements. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call (714) 741-5115. Funds are available on a 
first-come, first-served basis, a spokeswoman said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
