<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN SERIOUSLY HURT AFTER BEING SHOT IN SANTA ANA ALLEY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Santa Ana man was in serious condition Sunday after being shot repeatedly 
the day before while walking through an alley. 
</P>
<P>
 Juan Gonzalez was shot early Saturday at about 1:40 a.m. while walking through 
the alley in the 200 block of South Pacific Avenue shortly after visiting a 
nearby taco stand, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 He was in serious condition Sunday after surgery at Western Medical 
Center-Santa Ana, said Sgt. Dick Faust. Gonzalez, who police said is in his 
twenties, was shot in the neck, chest, abdomen, right arm and buttocks, Faust 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said they have no motives or suspects. 
</P>
