<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: EDITOR TO DISCUSS REBELLION IN MEXICO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRISTINA LIMA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sergio Munoz, editor of Nuestro Tiempo, the weekly Spanish-language 
publication of the Los Angeles Times, is scheduled to discuss the Mexican 
rebellion at the Spanish Hills Country Club in Camarillo at 6 p.m. Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 Munoz will discuss the Mexican state of Chiapas, where recent guerrilla 
movements have taken place. He will also discuss the relationship of the North 
American Free Trade Agreement to the revolt and the upcoming Mexican 
presidential election. 
</P>
<P>
 Munoz, who has traveled extensively in Chiapas, is also a writer for such 
publications as New Perspectives Quarterly and Jueves de Excelsior in Mexico 
City. 
</P>
<P>
 Those interested in attending the event, sponsored by the World Affairs 
Council of Ventura County, should make reservations by calling 648-1882. 
CHRISTINA LIMA 
</P>
</TEXT>
