<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: OXNARD; 1 KILLED, 4 HURT AS CAR ROLLS INTO FIELD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An 18-year-old Oxnard woman was killed early Sunday after the car she was 
traveling in left the roadway and rolled into a celery field along 5th Street, 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Patricia Perez was pronounced dead at the scene after she and two others were 
ejected from the car, investigators said. 
</P>
<P>
 Two other people in the car sustained injuries described as moderate to 
serious. 
</P>
<P>
 Oxnard police responded to the traffic accident about 12:30 a.m. Sunday along 
5th Street just west of Victoria Avenue. Investigators could not say what 
caused the car to leave the road or who was driving it. 
</P>
<P>
 Senior Deputy Coroner Craig Stevens said there is no indication that alcohol 
played a role in the crash but that toxicology tests would be done on Perez. 
</P>
<P>
 Perez, who was sitting in the left rear seat and was not wearing a seat belt, 
is survived by her parents and at least one brother, Stevens said. 
</P>
<P>
 Four other Oxnard residents were also injured in the accident, police said: 
Charles Rosales, 18; Victor Madueno, 18; Perla Ruiz, 23, and Dinnie Franco, 24. 
JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
</TEXT>
