<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: VENTURA; MAN LOSES CONTROL OF OF MOTORCYCLE, DIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By J. E. MITCHELL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Ventura man died early Sunday after losing control of his motorcycle while 
traveling on old Pacific Coast Highway near Rincon Beach, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Brian L. Dunn, 22, was traveling north when he drifted onto the shoulder and 
lost control of his motorcycle around 6:20 a.m., according to a California 
Highway Patrol spokeswoman. 
</P>
<P>
 Dunn, who was wearing a helmet, was taken to Ventura County Medical Center, 
where he underwent emergency surgery for massive head trauma and damage to 
other internal organs. CHP officials said he died in surgery a little more than 
two hours later. 
</P>
<P>
 The accident's cause had not been determined Sunday. J. E. MITCHELL 
</P>
</TEXT>
