<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: NEWBURY PARK, MOORPARK; PUBLIC HELP SOUGHT IN 
SOLVING THEFTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MATTHEW MOSK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 East Ventura County sheriff's detectives are looking for help from the public 
to solve several recent thefts, including the theft of a hot-air balloon from a 
Newbury Park apartment. 
</P>
<P>
 Detectives are offering a $1,000 reward for information that would solve the 
theft of the balloon, which was packed in a jet-ski trailer in the carport of 
the apartment complex in the 1800 block of West Hillcrest Drive. 
</P>
<P>
 Between Jan. 8 and 10, someone cut the chains locking the multicolored balloon 
and its basket to the carport, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 Detectives also are offering $1,000 for information leading to the arrest of 
three bicycle thieves who most recently forced the lock off a blue-green Huffy 
at 2:30 a.m. Jan. 6 from Spring Road in Moorpark. 
</P>
<P>
 Both rewards are part of the Sheriff's Department's Crime Stoppers program. 
People who call with information may remain anonymous and, if the information 
leads to an arrest with a criminal complaint filed, the caller will receive the 
reward. 
</P>
<P>
 The Crime Stoppers phone number is 494-TALK. MATTHEW MOSK 
</P>
</TEXT>
